        <item>
            <key> <string>_body</string> </key>
            <value> <string>"""\n
WARNING: this script requires proxy manager\n
\n
This script tries to acquire category values from other object\n
through reverse relation (ex. getAggregateRelatedValueList)\n
\n
base_category_list - list of category values we need to retrieve\n
object             - object which we want to assign roles to.\n
\n
TODO: how do be sure that the related object is already\n
indexed ? XXX\n
"""\n
category_dict = {}\n
\n
if object is None:\n
  return []\n
\n
for base_category in base_category_list:\n
  for o in object.getRelatedValueList(base_category):\n
    for user, role_list in o.get_local_roles():\n
      for role in role_list:\n
        if role in (\'Assignor\', \'Assignee\'):\n
          category_dict.setdefault(role, []).append(user)\n
\n
# By returning a dict, we force force ERP5Type\n
# to interprete the result as a mapping from\n
# roles to existing security groups \n
return category_dict\n
</string> </value>
